title: Vladislav Koulikov - Sambo Submission Fighting 4-6
description:
Vladislav Koulikov is one of the world's leading experts on the highly effective combat art of Russian Sambo. Sambo is renowned for its superior throws and ground fighting grappling submissions and no one is more qualified to teach you the lethal techniques of Sambo than Master Koulikov.

As a leading coach and competitor Master Koulikov is a highly respected fighter who has won numerous tournaments throughout the world including the 2004 North American Freestyle Sambo Middleweight Championship Title and the 1999 Grapplers Quest Middleweight Title. He has also been awarded the prestigious Grapplers Quest Most Technical Fighter Award! Master Koulikov is a several time NAGA Silver Medalist winner and has victories in many Ho-Holds-Barred no Gi events. He is a graduate of the famous Sambo 70 Academy in Moscow Russia where he learned his art and holds a 2nd Dan Black Belt in Judo and Tae Kwon Do. Master Koulikov is founder of the Ultimate Sambo Academy in Warrick New York where he teaches and trains.

Vol 4: Choking Submission Techniques
Vol 5: Mount, Side Mount, Scarf Hold Attacks and Escapes
Vol 6: Attacking the Back and Back Escapes
